The property is situated on Eurolink 31, a well established industrial estate on Mildred Sylvester Way, Normanton. The unit comprises a modern, steel
portal frame with a dual pitched roof, two-storey ancillary office space and open plan warehouse with ample parking.

Centre 31 comprises a modern, detached industrial unit constructed around a steel portal frame, beneath a pitched roof with part brick / part clad elevations. The unit is located within the well established Normanton Industrial Estate, benefitting from excellent access to the M62 via Junction 31 which lies within 0.5 miles. Junctions with the M1 and A1(M) are in close proximity, providing easy access to the region’s motorway network.

The scheme has full planning consent for a two unit scheme with consent for B1, B2 & B8 industrial / distribution uses set within 4.35 acres. Latitude is a prime opportunity for warehouse and industrial occupiers looking for well connected high quality space along the M62 corridor.

Howley Park Estate lies adjacent to the M62 Motorway at Morley, Leeds. The estate is a well established and successful business location providing over 700,000 sq ft of warehouse/industrial and office accommodation on a site of 120 acres. Existing occupiers include DSGi, Kodak, Keyline Builders Merchants, Stax Trade Centres, West Yorkshire Police and Asda.

62 Leeds is only ½ mile from J27 of M62 motorway which provides excellent access across the UK and feeds directly into the M1 motorway which is located only 5 miles to the east. J27 allows quick access to the M621 which provides quick access to Leeds City Centre, only 4 miles to the north east. Alternatively the site is accessed from Gelderd Road (A62) which is one of the main routes to Leeds.

The unit is a steel profile sheet clad warehouse constructed around a steel portal frame with a pitched roof. The property is located 1.75 miles south west of Leeds city centre and is within close proximity to the M621 (Junction 1), which in turn provides direct access to the M1 and M62 motorways. Gelderd Close is situated directly off Gelderd Road (A62) one of the main arterial routes into Leeds City Centre. This area of Gelderd Road is a well established mixed use area predominately motor trade, trade counter and industrial / warehousing occupiers.

The site is situated in an established industrial location, benefiting from excellent road communications located 1 mile from Junctions 4, 5 and 7 of the M621 and 1.5 miles from Junction 44 of the M1 and Leeds City Centre.

The property is a fully refurbished modern hybrid warehouse unit incorporating two storey office accommodation. The property is of steel portal framed construction with brickwork and profile sheet cladding to the elevations. The property is situated on the well-established Old Mill Business Park and prominently fronts the east side of the roundabout between Old Mill Lane and Gibraltar Island Road with access to the property directly off Bowcliffe Road. Old Mill Business Park lies approximately 1 mile to the south-east of Leeds City Centre and is easily accessible from Junction 7 of the M621 and Junction 44 of the M1 via the A639 (Pontefract Road). The surrounding area is well established covering a mixture of established commercial uses including industrial/warehousing, trade counters, offices and car showrooms.

The property comprises a steel portal framed industrial/warehouse unit with offices and canteen facilities. The warehouse area is arranged over four bays, the majority of which provides an eaves height of 9.2 metres and the remainder c5.0 metres. Access is provided by seven electric roller shutter doors which lead to drive-in internal loading area with tail-gate level access to the factory floor. Lighting is provided by sodium pod units and heating is by way of overhead gas fired hot air blowers. The property currently benefits froma power supply of 1,500 kva. The previous occupier utilised an additional supply providing a further 1,500 kva. The property is situated on a self contained and secure site of approximately 4.1 acres and benefits from substantial car parking and two dedicated access points.
